text: Ploger-Moneymaker Place, also known as Aambler, is a historic home located at Lebanon, Laclede County, Missouri. It was built about 1870, and is a two- story, "T"-shaped frame dwelling. It features a wraparound front porch supported by round columns and a two-story bay with decorative moulding. (includes 7 photographs from 1980) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1870 Category:Buildings and structures in Laclede County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Laclede County, Missouri Category:1870 establishments in Missouri
